message: Hello! Thank you for contacting Better Deal Insurance. My name is Chris. How can I assist you today?
Finally, I've been waiting for ages to speak with someone. My name is John and I need help with my policy.
Of course, John. I'm sorry to hear about the wait. Before proceeding, can you confirm your full name for security?
John Richardson
Thank you for completing security, John. Can you also confirm your date of birth?
Great, thank you. Just one more thing, could you please provide your first line of address and postcode?
12 Oak Street, AB1 23CD
Thank you for confirming. How can I assist you with your policy today, John?
I've been trying to make a claim for weeks now, and your online system keeps crashing. It's been so frustrating!

I'm really sorry to hear about the difficulties you've faced, John. Let's see how we can resolve this. A possible resolution could be to assist you with the claim manually. Would you like me to guide you through the process step by step?
Yes, please! I just want this sorted out as soon as possible.
I'm glad we could help. Let's go through the details together. Firstly, could you provide me with the details of the claim?
My claim is for a car accident that happened on the 15th of last month. I can provide all the necessary details.
Thank you for sharing that information, John. Let's work on getting this resolved for you. Please allow me a moment to review the details.
Take your time, but please hurry. I've wasted enough time on this already.
I understand your urgency, John. Thank you for your patience. I appreciate your cooperation.
Thank you. It's just been a really frustrating experience overall.
I completely understand, John. I want to assure you that we're on the same page in working towards a resolution. I value your feedback and thank you for bringing this to our attention.
I appreciate that, Chris. I just hope we can sort this out quickly.
We're doing our best to assist you efficiently, John. Thank you for your understanding. I'll propose a solution shortly. Please allow me a moment.
Thank you, Chris. I really need this sorted out soon.
